<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-10-12T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-10-12T18:00:00-05:00" n="23" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d23">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">702.0641/87: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Consul General at London (<persName type="from">Frazer</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-12T18:00:00-05:00">October 12, 1933—6 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your October 5, 4 p.m. Treasury Department states “It is not the
                                intention of this Department to make any general request of British
                                consular officers for information concerning the compensation paid
                                American citizens prior to the calendar year 1933, regardless of the
                                fact that British tax inspectors are seeking information as to
                                compensation paid British subjects for earlier periods.”</p>
                            <p>Endeavor to obtain reciprocal treatment for clerks in consular
                                offices. Retroactive effect was not intended by reciprocal
                                arrangement of June 28, 1933. Mail complete report.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>